e come to the end of their useful lives metal is always useful and can be infinitely recycled with out degradation of product the primary function at commercial metals ltd is the collection and processing of ferrous and non ferrous metals the recovery of scrap metals is an integral part of the recycling loop and helps to conserve our country’s valuable natural resources recent research of commercial construction waste found that more than  of steel was recycled however demand for steel products greatly outstrips supply from recycled sources so all recycled material will be used what is crucial to sustainability for steel is the level of recycling at the end of life at commercial metals ltd we work to convert scrap metals into the raw materials that other industries require to produce and manufacture new products we operate a modern efficent and professional scrap metal recycling yard that supplies to both domestic and international markets as a member of the scrap metal recycling association of new zealand we are committed to raising the standards within our industry and educating as to the important role that scrap metal recycling plays in helping to preserve our environment our friendly staff are highly skilled and our combined experience allow us to ensure that the job is done right the first time whilst offering our customers the assurance of stability honesty and all the benefits of an ongoing service metals are seperated into one of two basic grades which are referred to in the scrap metal recycling industry as ferrous and nonferrous metals once a metal has been indentified as one of these types it is then further categorized into more specific grades for processing we grade and process our metals according to international specifications which determine the price of the metal at the time of purchase please note that prices are regularly subject to change as dictated by the fluctuations in the world market and the nzdusd exchange rate   welcome what is scrap m